And Castro himself has pointed to the Chinese and Vietnamese cases as proof
that adapting Cuba's economy to current world conditions "does not imply a
return to capitalism."
Sino-Cuban trade ties are currently on the modest side. According to
Chinese diplomatic sources here, bilateral trade totalled about 250
million dollars in 1994, mainly Cuban sugar and Chinese food.
China would like to buy more Cuban sugar but Cuba has not been able to
meet the demand, after the past three harvests were among its historic
worst.
